            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35047",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mben",
                        "name": "mben",
                        "displayName": "Marc Bennewitz (GIATA mbH)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi\n\nCurrently I had a similar problem with Windows Live Mail 2008\/9 but after testing many different configuration I could fix it:\n-> mail.add_x_header = Off in php.ini\n\nI don't no if this was the bug described here \"http:\/\/bugs.php.net\/bug.php?id=48620\" or if this is an bug\/feature of the Mail Client.\nBut if it is activated the Client breaks parsing Mail after this Header and display the source starting on this position.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mben",
                        "name": "mben",
                        "displayName": "Marc Bennewitz (GIATA mbH)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-02T03:11:43.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-02T03:11:43.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36720",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=satoruyoshida",
                        "name": "satoruyoshida",
                        "displayName": "Satoru Yoshida",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi, xinghao.\r\n\r\nDo you use Chinese language with Zend_Mail? If so , I will be happy if you try followings.\r\n\r\n1)\r\nset encoding hz-gb-2312 (GB2312) or Big5 instead of UTF-8 to Zend_Mail().\r\n\r\n2)\r\nsetBodyText(mb_convert_encoding($txt, 'YOUR ENCODING', mb_detect_encoding($txt)) , $charset , $encoding );",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=satoruyoshida",
                        "name": "satoruyoshida",
                        "displayName": "Satoru Yoshida",
                        "active": true
                    },
